questionTemplates.text:
F: What's your brother's name?
M: His name is Robert.
{a}

M: I'd like to make an appointment with the doctor for tomorrow.
W: Unfortunately he is completely booked.
{a}

M: Are you going to join the swimming club this summer?
W: Swimming takes up too much of my time.
{a}

W: We are going to visit the flower exhibition tomorrow.
M: Are you? May I join you?
{a}

M: Gordon needs to find another place to live. The apartment he rents now has been sold to a new owner.
W: He'd better start looking right away. When all the students come back in a few weeks, he won't find any near the campus.
{a}

M: Driving at night always makes me tired. Let's stop for dinner.
W: Fine. And let's find a motel, so that we can get an early start tomorrow.
{a}

M: Good morning. Can I help you?
F: I'd like to buy a pair of shoes for my son.
{a}

M: Do you feel like watching the evening news?
W: You ought to stay away from me. I have a bad cold and wouldn't want you to catch it.
{a}

M: Did you go shopping alone yesterday?
W: No, my sister went with me.
{a}

W: I want to invite more friends to the party, what do you think?
M: The more, the happier.
{a}

M: Did you hear that over 300 people applied for the entry-level job at Show's Department Store?
W: Oh, really. It's a dog-eat-dog world out there.
{a}

W: Do you know what time the bread shop opens?
M: It usually opens at half past six, but on Sunday it opens half an hour later.
{a}

M: You look tired. Where did you go last night?
W: I planned to watch a film, but I went to meet my friend at the airport.
{a}

W: Looks like rain. Better look for your umbrella.
M: Yeah, I think it's definitely going to rain. That's why I'm not going out.
{a}

F: Mary's handwriting is very well.
M: Yes, she is. But Li Ping's handwriting is the best in their class.
{a}

F: We'd like to sit near the window if that's possible.
M: I'm afraid all the tables there are taken. We'd better change one.
{a}

F: Excuse me, sir. What time is it now?
M: Sorry, my watch doesn't work.
{a}

M: Can you speak German?
W: Yes, I can. I speak it very well. But I know a little Italian.
{a}

W: De you really mean that you want to give up the job?
M: Well, I'll give it a second thought.
{a}

W: The man at the garage thinks that I take good care of my car.
M: So do I. I don't see any scratches on the outside and the inside is clean,too.
{a}

W: Did you forget about my birthday, honey?
M: How could I? I've booked a table in Michael's restaurant for this evening. And I'll pick you up from work. Happy birthday!
{a}

W: The letter of credit will be opened in your favor within 10 working days from the date of the contract.
M: All right. I accept your terms. I hope everything turns out Okay.
{a}

F: Hello, can I speak to Tom?
M: Sorry, he isn't in.
{a}

W: Are you busy on Friday night, Jack?
M: Well ... uh ... I haven't got any definite plans yet. Why?
{a}

W: Have you ever put a computer together before?
M: No, never. But I think if we follow these instructions exactly, we won't have much trouble.
{a}

M: I missed the bus again today because I turned the alarm clock off in my sleep.
W: Try putting it far away from your bed and you'll get up on time.
{a}
